Class Performance

java.lang.Object
  Performance

public class Performance
extends java.lang.Object

Author:
Patrick Behrens Performance is a set of tests that measures the elapsed time of a specified number of insertions and retrievals into Maps. This Test class test both the variety of hashCode functions, a variety of concrete implementations of the Map interface, and a variety of insertions and retrievals from those Maps.

doMeasure

public static void doMeasure(java.lang.String label,
                             java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Integer> map,
                             int n,
                             int r)
An auxiliary method that inserts a specific number, n, of keys from longList, measures the performance for a given large number, r, of retrievals from longList, and prints the result using the given label.

Parameters:
label - The text to print before the performance result.
map - The concrete implementation of the Map interface used for insertions and retrievals.
n - The number of insertions in longList.
r - The number of retrievals from longList.
